Cryptocurrency Rewards
Introduction
Cryptocurrency rewards are a way to earn cryptocurrency for contributing GPU power to the Petals network. Petals uses the cryptocurrency rewards to help fund the development and maintenance of the network.
Prerequisites
To use the cryptocurrency rewards feature, you will need the following:
A cryptocurrency wallet
A membership in a cryptocurrency mining pool
How to use the crypto_rewards.py module
To use the crypto_rewards.py module, follow these steps:
Install the crypto_rewards.py module.
Set the following environment variables:
PETALS_CRYPTO_REWARDS_PUBLIC_KEY: The public key used to verify cryptocurrency reward signatures.
PETALS_CRYPTO_REWARDS_PRIVATE_KEY: The private key used to sign cryptocurrency reward requests.
Run the crypto_rewards.py module.
The crypto_rewards.py module will automatically contribute GPU power to the Petals network and earn cryptocurrency rewards.
Troubleshooting
If you are having trouble using the crypto_rewards.py module, try the following troubleshooting tips:
Make sure that you have set the PETALS_CRYPTO_REWARDS_PUBLIC_KEY and PETALS_CRYPTO_REWARDS_PRIVATE_KEY environment variables correctly.
Make sure that you are using a valid cryptocurrency wallet.
Make sure that you are a member of a cryptocurrency mining pool.
Make sure that your computer has enough GPU power to contribute to the Petals network.
If you are still having trouble, please reach out to the Petals team for support.
Conclusion
AI Satoshi's second phase revolves around propelling AI Satoshi towards superintelligence by constructing a decentralized network of high-performance computing resources. 
